# Hygiene rules for lingokids/lk-analysis-assets (PUBLIC REPO)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# This repo is public on github.com/lingokids — any file committed here is
# visible to anyone on the internet. These patterns block accidental commits
# of files that contain customer identifiers, PII, or sensitive internal terms.
#
# To add a new pattern: file a Slack note in #sherlock-ai-hackathon-data
# explaining what's being blocked. Don't silently broaden — every rule has a
# reason that needs to be discoverable.

# ── Customer / user identifiers ─────────────────────────────────────────
*user_id_*
*user-id-*
*customer_*
*customer-*
*uid_*
*uid-*

# Email addresses embedded in filenames
*@*lingokids.com*
*@gmail.com*
*@hotmail.com*
*@yahoo.com*

# Stripe / payment identifiers
*sub_*.png
*cus_*.png
*ch_*.png
*pi_*.png

# Personal / dev exploration that shouldn't be public
scratch/
draft/
private/
*.private.*

# Editor / OS noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
.idea/
.vscode/

# Large binaries (LFS or other storage instead)
*.mp4
*.mov
*.avi
*.iso
*.tar.gz

# Secrets — should never be committed anywhere, but extra-paranoid here
*.env
*.env.*
secrets.json
*token*.txt
*credentials*

# Notebook outputs (often contain stray data dumps)
*.ipynb_checkpoints/

# ── What IS allowed here ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Aggregate chart PNGs (waterfall, WoW progression, dashboard exports)
# Sized-driver tables with NO customer-level rows
# Sim payloads (test fixtures with placeholder data)
# README documentation
# Investigation summary screenshots — only if pre-redacted
